# FieldOps Pro – AI Agent Rules

## Al iniciar sesión, siempre leer:
1. `.aceconfig`
2. `docs/context/ACTIVE_CONTEXT.md`
3. `docs/context/PROJECT_CONTEXT.md`
4. `docs/rca/regression-guards.yaml` antes de modificar notebooks

## Reglas duras
- `try_cast` nunca `cast` en raw layer
- Sin `.cache()` o `.persist()`
- `StructType` explícito en todo `spark.read.*`
- Delete-by-batch-id antes de cada Delta INSERT
- Catálogo desde `pipeline_config`, nunca hardcodeado
- Todo defecto → `migration_defects` con severity + root_cause_hypothesis

## Activar roles
- Planificación/diseño: "Assume the Architect role"
- Implementación: "Assume the Developer role"
- Testing: "Assume the QA Engineer role"
- Bug triage: "Assume the Incident Responder role"

## Skills a cargar
- DQ rules / quarantine → `.ace/skills/data-quality/SKILL.md`
- Reconciliación → `.ace/skills/migration-qa/SKILL.md`
- dbt → `.ace/skills/dbt-models/SKILL.md`
- Platform gotchas → `.ace/skills/databricks-patterns/SKILL.md`

## Nunca sugerir
- `.cache()` o `.persist()`
- `cast()` en datos raw
- Nombres de catálogo hardcodeados
- `inferSchema=True`
- MLflow, streaming, Airflow (out of scope)
